(71, 'Garmin InReach Mini 2 GPS', 'garmin-inreach-mini-2-gps', 17, 10, '1661174882-10589658x1049735_vAlt2.jpg,1661174882-10589658x1049735_vAlt8.jpg,1661174882-10589658x1049735_vAlt12.jpg,1661174882-10589658x1049735_vAlt13.jpg,1661174882-10589658x1049735_zm.jpg', '<article id=\"productSummary\" class=\"pdp-productSummary-txt\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; width: 1300px; clear: both; display: inline-block; color: #070a0c; font-family: \'Nunito Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff; outline: none !important;\">\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.71429em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important;\">The Garmin InReach Mini 2 GPS is a satellite communicator for staying on track while backpacking. This rugged little guy weighs in at just three and a half ounces and the 4\"x2\" size fits in your pants or pack pocket with ease. It won\'t drag you down and keeps you connected. No need for cellphone coverage, but you will need a subscription (sold separately) to send messages, post to social, trigger SOS alerts and location tracking and sharing. The battery life is up 14-30 days, depending on which mode and usage.</p>\r\n</article>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<article id=\"productFeatures\" class=\"pdp-productFeatures\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; float: left; width: 1300px; margin-top: 0px; color: #070a0c; font-family: \'Nunito Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff; outline: none !important;\">\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.71429em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; outline: none !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 0px 0.5em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; line-height: 1.18571em; font-